Lately I feel disoriented...like I'm drunk. When I look at things or when I'm driving I have to think about it alittle more than normal. Maybe my brain is just deteriorating. great!

I can't stand that I only do the things I love occasionally. I wish I could paint and write constantly, but I feel like I don't have anything to paint or write. It sounds pathetic and I guess it might be, but I hate not having anything in my head.

ABSENT

I've been painting my nails and buying pretty jewelry/accesories. It's nice to stare at, thinking maybe it will help/give me something.


.brandy.

Update...
I have Strep Throat. It's pretty awesome... sike!
Me and my Dad stayed home sick together yesterday. We're cool like that I guess.

way to bring in February. yeah.

p.s.
take your vitamins!!!

.brandy.

I remember looking at the "under 21 until 8-11-07" on my license forever ago and thinking 2007 is sooo far away. 
It's here now and it came so fast.

Last night was extremely RANDOM.
We got to a party at 7 seconds until midnight.
I remember going everywhere in/out polk county, and playing with a dog named Booger.
I fell asleep sitting straight up on a couch with 4 other people and woke up freeeeezing.
Today was just for relaxing... Pizza, Ultimate Fighting, lots of naps, and Blackeye Peas w/ rice.

2007 is going to be fun. duhh.


.brandy.

I've been up since 6:30am.
It's 4:06am now.
I'm not tired, but I want to go to sleep.

This year we decided not to go with the traditional Christmas.
Instead of an Evergreen Fern we have a 9 ft. palm tree decorated. 
We usually have all of our family over on Christmas day, but not this year.
Tomorrow night (tech. tonight) will make up for it though.

I've been more crafty lately.
Curtains, drawing, stitching, writing.
looking/seeing.

Jenni was here for a week... not long enough.
We had a valuable conversation.
I guess we are adults these days.

I haven't been to a Rodeo in so long.
I really want to go soon.
That's where it's at.

4:37am now.
I'm dozing off finally.

I wish there was someone that could/would move somewhere/anywhere with me in August.
I just want to go go go!
That's all.

.brandy.

I'm in South Carolina.
It's cold, but no snow yet.
I drove pretty much the whole way... my dad drove to Jacksonville, and I drove the rest of the way to  Charleston.

We have an awesome view of I-26 from our suite... sike! 
My dad said that if it snows we'll appreciate our view b/c then we'll get to see all the ppl on the interstate try to drive in the snow. ha. entertainment.

Everyone have a happy Thanksgiving!


.brandy.

It's like we don't know what to do with ourselves.
We walk around aimlessly.
I feel as if there is no satisfaction with life right now.
I think this is all setting in slowly. It's creeping up.
Then one day it's going hit me, and I'll break into little pieces.
Until that day comes, "I'm ok."

like...
The ghost of a complete stranger.


.brandy.

Nothing can REALLY prepare you for something like this. You can know for years that this day is coming way sooner than it is supposed to, and it will still break your heart. 

I've been preparing for this since I was sixteen. 
Four years later...
Today just broke my heart.
My chest is aching.
My eyes are swollen.

but everything is ok. it really is. 
my mom has finally been healed, 
and I know she is smiling.

God,
I understand.



.brandy.

Last night was incredible.
BROKEN SOCIAL SCENE was so amazing.
and so is Tamosso!

Errrca, Jared, Gabe, and me waited around after the show with Tamosso. We waited forever, but it was worth it... 
when Andrew (one of the guitarist from BROKEN SOCIAL SCENE) was walking to their bus Tamosso ran up behind him, smacked his butt, and yelled "I LOVE YOU!!"... it was deff. worth the wait. 

and I decided last night that every boy there is my boyfriend.
such cute boys.


.brandy.

I don't believe in ghost, but yesterday made me think.
I was in my parents room and I saw a shadow in the shape of a body between the stairs and the dresser. and there was no one in the room but me. then the shadow disappeared and I felt a rush of cool air. 
it was very strange, but I still don't believe in ghost.

I wish that Halloween lasted all year.
Last night I was a BEAR and tonight I'm going to be THE TOOTH FAIRY.
It's nice being something other than yourself.


...an absolute.

.brandy.

weird happenings.
extremely intense dreams.
I felt drunk all day yesterday... and I hadn't a sip.
Everything seemed so far away. 
Distant from reality I guess.

I made my halloween costume last night.
I'm the TOOTH FAIRY.

The air conditioning broke on Thursday. 
Our house feels like the inferno... until Monday.


Tonight will be awesome. I'm going to see MEWITHOUTYOU.

I'm out.
BK lounge, don't worry I'm on my way.


.brandy.

Front porch realizations.

I just don't care anymore.
I've lost my "glow".... Joy. well that's what I was told.

Some days are better than others.
I wish I  knew what made them better.
If I knew what made certain days better I probably wouldn't want to yell so much.
I've been getting angry easily.
AGGRESSIVE.

Tomorrow I'm suppose to have a list of characteristics that I find in people of interest, but I can't really think of anything particular.... just the basics.

I'm boring...  I'm ok with that.
Goodnight.

.brandy.

I had a major break through within myself tonight.
I think differently than most.
I am Paranoid... I am a lot of things.
I am affection resistant.
I can be bitter and bright all at once.
I am a dreamer.
I have a sixth sense.

"you're an enigma wrapped in a riddle, inside a mystery."
-jose


People that try to understand and genuinely want to understand...
People that are sincere are my favorite.


.brandy.

I want to know why some people are so significant in peoples lives.
I've been asking myself "why do I still talk to...?" or "why are they in my life?" and "what purpose do I serve in their life?"

I still think everything happens for a reason, and people come in and out of our lives for a reason.

Slight stomach ache... continuous for days.
I know this feeling.
somethings going to happen.
probably not good.


.brandy.

and PawPaw... well, he's 70 and still "off the chain"!

vigor.

little things like that really get to me, and the bigger problems that should get to me, don't get to me at all.
hmmm.

GAIN joyful expressions... that's where it's at!!!

so much going on... inside and out.
life is going to be different soon.

I got rid of my mask, and for now I'm ok with that.
I can deal.



I feel so familiar lately. It feels like I know what's going on... what's going to happen. Like it's happened before. Maybe I'm just prepared. 
I am.

I love the way my laundry smells.

.brandy.

I'm 20 now.
I don't know how I feel about that.

Things are ok.

My Nana and Paw-Paw made turning 20 and all the things I've been through along the way worth it.
On my Birthday they gave me a bunch of pictures of me and my parents through out the years. It was awesome to look at those and actually remember how things were back then. It made me feel better and worse at the same time. Better b/c I could actually see proof of happiness. Worse b/c I couldn't remember those times without the pictures. It's sad when you can only remember what things were like yesterday and not just a few years ago. 
But now I can look at those pictures whenever I'm unable to remember better times.

They also gave me my Uncle Joe's scrapbooks that he made before he died. I think they knew that I would appreciate them the most.
And to add to the thoughtfulness that went into these gifts, they gave me 2 Johnny Cash, 3 Dolly Parton, 3 Merle Haggard albums... all on Vinyl.

....
I'm 2 days into something///should be interesting.
maybe I'll be able to throw this mask away.

.brandy.

you can be happy. i promise.


.brandy.

I think I have Insomnia.
I haven't been able to sleep for more than five consecutive hours recently.
It's like my body is tired, but IT WONT SLEEP. 
I don't like this.

.brandy.

I'm in Baltimore, Maryland. It's so neat here... all of the hills and the big cities. We saw a Deer from the window of our room yesterday. I swear we walked like 5,000 miles today in Washington D.C. My feet hurt so bad. 
We ended the night with nothing less than an amazing show... The Weakerthans and The New Amsterdams. Tomorrow we are going on a nature hike/walk outside of Baltimore. It should be nice. 

Yesterday we went to an awesome record store. They had everything on vinyl.

The subway/metro is fun!

.brandy.

Today we are leaving for Washington D.C. It's weird to know that we are actually leaving today. I feel like this is one of those awesome trips you talk about with your friends, but you never really go. We are going to see The Weakerthans and The New Amsterdams. Me and Jenni did a photoshoot yesterday. It was fun, but really hot.


.brandy.

I needed that. 
thank you.
Walk.


...

Erica, Jenni, Felicia, and I leave for Washington D.C. on Sunday. 
I'm so excited.
...

.brandy.

I've really been thinking alot lately about getting out of here.
I'm going to try to transfer to Flagler College in St. Augustine.
Everytime I think about it I get a panic feeling, but I'm hoping that won't get to me.
I really feel like I have to do this.

.brandy.

It's nice.

ok, so how can so many unfortunate things happen to one person?
Do I have bad Karma?
maybe. whatever.

I am really angry right now. 
I don't deserve this.
I do good things for people all of the time. Maybe I'm selfish for even thinking that I deserve better for doing good deeds. I am.

Conclusion...
I am subconsciously selfish, and I deserve whatever.
NOT!

I just want something good to happen. I really do.
I want to be happy about something for a while.

.brandy.

I just saw the worst commercial... GUYS GONE WILD!... springbreak. Gross.

I went to a gay club tonight with one of my gay friends. It was alot of fun and very entertaining. I saw my first drag show tonight... hillarious! 
Those girls/guys, whatever they were, amazed me. They can walk better in high heels than I can...pshh.

sleep.

p.s...... I QUIT! YEAH I SAID IT... I QUIT!

I had lunch with my cousin and the most amazing canadian ever.

painpainpain.

i love remembering.

tonight i ran a red light, and it wasn't a light that had just changed. it was red for at least 20 seconds. i could have easily been killed, but the road was deserted. 
there are reasons for everything.

i have plans.
several.


.brandy.

What makes people do that stupid maneuver in crosswalks at grocery stores, intersections, ect... 
it's like a twist of the hips and a shuffling of the feet. People walk very slowly and then once they get about halfway across they do that stupid "walk fast, stop" for about 2 seconds, and then they start walking extremely slow again.

If your going to walk slow. Walk slow.
If your going to walk fast. Walk fast the entire time!

.brandy.
